This paper deals with learning probabilistic models for ranking data, which is a problem that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper presents a polynomial time algorithm for learning the parameters of a mixture of two Mallows models, which involves techniques from linear algebra and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves some information theory and signal processing concepts, which could make cs.IT (Information Theory) a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with ranking data in a heterogeneous population, which could make cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a relevant sub-category as well.
